  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlockPoolSlice
    A block pool slice represents a portion of a block pool stored on a volume.

    This class is a container of multiple thread pools, each for a volume, so that we can schedule async disk operations easily.
    FsDatasetCache
    Manages caching for an FsDatasetImpl by using the mmap(2) and mlock(2) system calls to lock blocks into memory.

    This class is a container of multiple thread pools, one for each non-RamDisk volume with a maximum thread count of 1 so that we can schedule async lazy persist operations easily with volume arrival and departure handled.
